Usage: waldo/helpers/remote.py [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
Options:
  -ap  --autoplay       Args: Button number
                        Autoplay track with button number according to config list 'buttons'.

  -cal --calibrate      Args: None
                        Set USB numpad or MCP analog reader as button input - reset and recalibrate buttons.

  -h  --help            Args: None
                        Show this message and exit.

General:
  Connect raspberryPi with "analog keyboard" Rigby before starting the raspberryPi; before running scripts/remote.py.
  If you changed the length of the cable, run command "python scripts/remote.py -cal". Restart raspberryPi or scripts/remote.py.
  Buttons get their commands from the main config file (list "buttons").
